      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety warnings and instructions before use.</strong> Failure to follow them may result in electric shock, fire, and/or serious injury. Save all warnings and instructions for future reference.
      </div>

      <h3>Work Area &amp; Electrical</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep the work area clean and well lit; clutter and darkness invite accidents.</li>
        <li>Do not operate in explosive atmospheres (flammable liquids, gases, or dust).</li>
        <li>Keep children and bystanders away while operating.</li>
        <li>Do not expose the tool to rain or wet conditions.</li>
        <li>When a battery pack is not in use, keep it away from metal objects (clips, coins, keys, nails) that could short the terminals and cause burns or fire.</li>
        <li>Recharge only with the Bosch charger specified for the pack.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Personal Safety</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Stay alert; do not operate while tired or under the influence of drugs, alcohol, or medication.</li>
        <li>Always wear eye protection and a dust mask, and work only in a well-ventilated area.</li>
        <li>Ensure the switch is OFF before inserting the battery pack or carrying the tool.</li>
        <li>Do not wear loose clothing, jewelry, or gloves near moving parts; keep hair clear.</li>
        <li>Do not overreach; keep proper footing and balance.</li>
        <li>Remove any adjusting key or wrench before turning the tool on.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Router-Specific Rules</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Clamp the workpiece</strong> to a stable platform and guide the tool with both hands. Never hold the workpiece in one hand and the tool in the other.</li>
        <li>Never place hands near or below the cutting surface.</li>
        <li>Never lay the workpiece on a hard surface (concrete, stone) &mdash; a protruding bit can make the tool jump.</li>
        <li>Make sure the work surface is free of nails and foreign objects.</li>
        <li>Use only router bits whose rated speed is at least equal to the router's maximum no-load speed. Bits run too fast can break and fly apart.</li>
        <li>The cutter diameter must be at least 1/4" smaller than the opening for the bit and cutter.</li>
        <li>Never start the tool with the bit engaged in the material.</li>
        <li>Never use dull or damaged bits; they require more force and can snap.</li>
        <li>Never touch the bit during or immediately after use &mdash; it is too hot to handle.</li>
        <li>Never lay the tool down until the motor has come to a complete stop.</li>
        <li>After changing bits or making adjustments, confirm the collet nut and all adjustment devices are securely tightened.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Feed direction matters.</strong> Viewed from the top, the bit rotates clockwise, so the cutting feed must be counter-clockwise. Feeding in the wrong direction causes the bit to climb out of the work and pull the tool along. Inside and outside cuts require different feed directions &mdash; see "Feeding the Router."
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Dust hazard.</strong> Dust from sanding, sawing, grinding, and drilling can contain chemicals known to cause cancer or reproductive harm (e.g., lead from paint, crystalline silica from masonry, arsenic/chromium from treated lumber). Work in a well-ventilated area with an approved particulate dust mask.
      </div>

      <h2>Functional Description</h2>

      <p>
        The Bosch palm router is a one-handed-form-factor edge router designed for 1/4" shank bits.
        It handles edge forming, grooving, and sign making, and is ideal for trimming laminates,
        phenolics, and other materials bonded to a substrate (typically overhanging by about 1/8" / 3 mm).
      </p>

      <div class="warning">
        Disconnect the battery pack from the tool before making any assembly, adjustments, or accessory changes. This reduces the risk of accidental starting.
      </div>

